  "elapsed_s": 5.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So anyway so when Bernard's family went to Warsaw, I went to Siedlce, I came to Warsaw, got my-- and that's how maybe two or three times-- this was in March already, 1940-- and brought those-- there's another thing.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The wall was already on in Warsaw.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I had friends of mine-- their parents lived on [NON-ENGLISH], which was a small ghetto-- I don't know if anybody knows about it-- a small ghetto that was liquidated into the big ghetto.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But they lived right at the small ghetto.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So I stayed with them.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Bernard would come, and I- I would go and get my paint.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "This was, you know, this was an awful lot of black market going on in the ghetto, too-- fortunately, otherwise people would starve even more.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I bought those two-- I don't know how heavy they are, another 50 pounds maybe.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I don't know, you know those big cans of paint, house paint, and went to stay the evening with those friends of mine from [NON-ENGLISH]-- that family.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And Bernard would come in the evening.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Of course, we had the nice visit, and at about midnight-- the train was going back, I think, about 5 or 4 o'clock in the morning.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So at midnight I would climb through that walls, and Bernard and another friend of ours, [NON-ENGLISH], would-- on the-- on the cord would lift those paints over the wall and then I would pick it up and go the-- but I did it maybe two or three times, and then Passover was coming.",
      "word_count": 54
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I went home for the holidays and I got typhus.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
